"leak_canary_help_detail" : "A memory leak is a programming error that causes your application to keep a reference to an object that is no longer needed. As a result, the memory allocated for that object cannot be reclaimed, eventually leading to an OutOfMemoryError crash.

For instance, an Android activity instance is no longer needed after its onDestroy() method is called, and storing a reference to that activity in a static field would prevent it from being garbage collected.

LeakCanary identifies an object that is no longer needed and finds the chain of references that prevents it from being garbage collected.

To fix a memory leak, you need to look at that chain and find which reference is causing the leak, i.e. which reference should have been cleared at the time of the leak. LeakCanary highlights with a red underline wave the references that are the possible causes of the leak.

Tap on each reference row for more details, tap again to close."

"leak_canary_help_detail" : "Ein Memory-Leak ist ein Programmierfehler der dafür sorgt, dass deine Anwendung eine Referenz auf ein Objekt hält, das nicht länger benötigt wird. Daraus folgt, dass der Speicher der dem Objekt zugewiesen wurde nicht wieder freigegeben wird, was eventuell zu einem OutOfMemoryError-Absturz führt.

Eine Instanz einer Android-Activity wird nicht mehr benötigt, nachdem ihre onDestroy() Methode aufgerufen wurde. Würde man eine Referenz auf diese Activity in einem statischen Feld speichern, dann wird der durch die Activity genutzte Speicher nicht mehr durch den Garbage Collector freigegeben.

LeakCanary identifiziert ein Objekt, dass nicht länger benötigt wird und findet die Kette an Referenzen die es davon abhält seinen Speicher freizugeben.

Um ein Memory-Leak zu beheben, musst du anhand der Kette herausfinden, welche Referenz für das Leak verantwortlich ist, d.h. welche Referenz beim Auftreten des Leaks bereinigt sein soll. LeakCanary hebt Referenzen die mögliche Ursachen für das Memory-Leak sein könnten mit einer roten Wellenlinie hervor.

Tippe auf eine Zeile mit einer Referenz um mehr Details anzuzeigen, tippe noch einmal um die Details zu schließen."

playstore_details.title: THE LEGO® MOVIE 2™ Movie Maker
playstore_details.description:
BUILD your LEGO® movie scene, RECORD, EDIT your movie and SHARE! 

Do you want to become a LEGO® Movie Maker? Now you can with THE LEGO® MOVIE 2™ Movie Maker app. 
Create any movie you want – exciting, funny, action-packed and more! – quickly and easily on your phone. You can even add sounds and visual effects to your live video footage! 

Get the special LEGO® Movie Maker set to make your own movie scenes from the THE LEGO® MOVIE 2™ featuring EMMET, LUCY and more. Just download the app, build your very own LEGO movie scene, record your movie, edit and share with friends and family! 

It’s simple and safe to use and provides hours of entertainment. LEGO® Movie Maker gives kids everything they need to make awesome LEGO movies. 

Important information
THE LEGO® MOVIE 2™ Movie Maker app is FREE to download. 
The app is available for phone only. 
The app is suitable for kids from 8 years and up. 
All movies are moderated before being shared and movies revealing personally identifiable information are rejected. 
There’s no third-party advertising. 
LEGO marketing content and information is served in hope of inspiring children’s creative play.

To fully enjoy the app and share movies, kids need a parent or guardian’s permission to create a LEGO Account. 
As part of the LEGO Account sign-up, we will collect the following information: 
- The country in which you live 
- Your email address 
- Date of birth 

We will utilize your personal information to manage your account and review anonymized data to provide a safe, contextualized and excellent LEGO experience. You can learn more here http://aboutus.lego.com/legal-notice/Privacy-Policy and here http://aboutus.lego.com/en-us/legal-notice/terms-of-use-for-apps Our privacy policy and terms of use for apps are accepted if you download this app.
